Title : Bert Beyens
Text : <!-- Do not use the "prod blp/dated" template directly; the above line is generated by "subst:prod blp|reason" -->
'''Bert Beyens''' (°1956) is a [[Belgium|Belgian]] filmmaker, known for ''Jan Cox A Painter's Odyssey'' (written and directed with Pierre De Clercq, Belgium The Netherlands 1988), and ''A la Rencontre de Marcel Hanoun'' (France 1994). <ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm0079888</ref>  He  teaches writing and directing at RITS since 1993. Between 2001 and 2013 he was the head of RITS, Erasmus University College Brussels.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ritstv.be/lessonsinfilm/biobeyens.htm |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-05-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504224848/http://www.ritstv.be/lessonsinfilm/biobeyens.htm |archivedate=2014-05-04 |df= }}</ref> He was Vice President for Finance and Fundraising CILECT (The International Association of Film and Television Schools) between 2008 and 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rits.be/docenten/bert-beyens |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-05-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140504225011/http://www.rits.be/docenten/bert-beyens |archivedate=2014-05-04 |df= }}</ref> Since 2014 Bert Beyens is the Chair of the Executive Council of GEECT (Groupement Européen des Ecoles de Cinéma et de Télévision/European Grouping of FIlm and Television Schools), and prior to that held the post of treasurer (2010–2014). <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cilect.org/groups/view/352 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-05-04 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320133223/http://www.cilect.org/groups/view/352 |archivedate=2014-03-20 |df= }}</ref> In addition he is also a member of the European Film Academy.<ref>http://www.europeanfilmacademy.org/Presentation.presentation.0.html?&no_cache=1&uid=104</ref>

